Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer* position with *Angi*. I bring over four years of professional experience building full-stack, production-grade systems — including LLM-powered features and microservices integrations — along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a full-stack LLM-powered MCP integration layer that translates natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1,000+ RESTful API endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and reliable execution across a distributed microservices surface. To keep these systems production-ready, I implemented a full observability stack using Langfuse and LangSmith, covering tracing, structured logging, and evaluation hooks, reducing end-to-end latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50% through targeted concurrency and routing optimizations. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to the backbone infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications — delivering full-stack microservices features with scalable relational database design across Agile sprints. I also designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Java, PostgreSQL, and Redis handling file operations across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO, and developed AWS Step Functions workflows to orchestrate long-running distributed data import jobs — both requiring the kind of systems-level thinking and operational stability focus this role demands. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to Angi's core engineering responsibilities: building and shipping reliable full-stack features, architecting scalable microservices, and driving LLM-powered product direction.

My research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture Angi values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I managed the full model lifecycle from training to reliable inference via vLLM and Hugging Face, and led workshops on AI Agent development with LangChain, LangGraph, and LangSmith for 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to translate complex technical concepts into clear, accessible language for diverse audiences — directly mirroring the cross-functional communication and knowledge-sharing responsibilities central to this role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to Angi's product-engineering team.

I have always been passionate about building technology that creates real, tangible value for everyday people — and Angi's mission of making home care easy by connecting homeowners with reliable pros, and helping pros find the winnable work they want, resonates deeply with me. I envision myself contributing my talent to furthering Angi's goal of becoming the single trusted destination for everything home. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

